revision.text:
==Details==
===Description=== Shards are an item dropped when defeating any kind of Pokémon. These typed shard can be invested into the Shards tab to increase type effectivity, and your damage output.
===Upgrades=== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! To Purchase Level !! Shard Cost |- | 1 || 500 |- | 2 || 1000 |- | 3 || 1500 |- | 4 || 2000 |- | 5 || 2500 |- | 6 || 3000 |- | 7 || 3500 |- | 8 || 4000 |- | 9 || 4500 |- | 10 || 5000 |}
To max out an entire tree is 110,000 of the respective shard type.
==Methods== ===Helpful tips=== The shard types reflect whatever type(s) the Pokémon defeated were. Defeating Pokémon in a Dungeon give you 3 Shards of whatever types the Pokémon was, however defeating the boss will give you 20 Shards. Pokémon in Gyms give you 5 shards each, and Wild Pokémon on Routes give you 1.
====Optimal farming routes==== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Type !! Route !! Chance |- |Normal || 1 || 100% |- |Fire || 112 || 50% |- |Water || 19 || 100% |- |Electric || 110 || 25% |- |Grass || 15 || 44.4% |- |Ice || 217 || 44.4% |- |Fighting || 217 || 33.3% |- |Poison || 15 || 66.7% |- |Ground || 111 || 55.6% |- |Flying || 115 || 60% |- |Psychic || 211 || 25% |- |Bug ||30 || 50% |- |Rock || 214 || 23.5% |- |Ghost || 209 || 11.8% |- |Dragon || 45 || 8.3% |- |Dark || 101 || 33.3% |- |Steel || 113 || 33.3% |- |Fairy || 112 || 50% |- |}
=====Kanto Gyms=====
